Jaundice is harmless and usually clears up quickly.  If your baby has jaundice, it’s best not to use any remedies, and to let a doctor or nurse take care of it.  You can do your best to keep your baby comfortable by following a few simple guidelines:

  • keep your baby’s room as dark as possible, but not too dark;
  • make sure your baby gets plenty of rest, sleep, and sunshine;
  • keep your baby warm.

